column12: Measurement condition : Ice; Cloudy , Light Rain , Light Wind Blowing Downstream
column13: Flow isolated to the side channel.  Large Blizzard has filled in and frozen the main channel.  Looks like the water piled up and eroded a channel past the gauge shelter to the side channel.  Furthermore, it appears that the extra flow from gauge pool to side channel has eroded a fair amount of soil/vegetation/small rocks.  High liklihood that the conditions will warrant a new rating.  Once the area completely thaws, as many open water measurements as possible should be obtained.
column14: Poor quality wading measurement of side channel.  No signs of flow from main channel as it is under ice and snow.  No signs of erosion or sound of flow.  Walked d/s, following cavern eroded out of the snow down closer to the lake.  Visually didn't look like any extra water. @ Uncertainty: IVE method, 2-sigma value (2 x Uncertainty Value reported in *.ft File). @

column12: Measurement condition : Ice; Clear , No Precipitation , Light Wind Blowing Upstream
column13:
-Mostly open between gauge pool and first main drop although there are patches of thinner shore ice along some parts of that stretch. B conditions likely.
-Gauge pool with 15cm thick ice above measurement section and frozen where streams converge just before lake
-Side channel running and open
column14: -FT2 wade at usual section with side channel included -Plotting of channels for measurement will be backwards as side channel to RHB of main flow measured afterwards -Lots of QA/QC warnings. To be expected at such a small, shallow, stream with bouldery substrate. FT2 still a better option as fully submerging cups and avoiding rocks difficult with conventional. -Had to clear ice from measurement section. Lifted broken ice out of channel to try and avoid affecting backwater increase. -Anomalies in velocity profile align with center point of upstream boulders that are embedded in ice. -Levels only run once but rod placed in water before measurement and cut observed pre/post with no change (0.069m both times) @ Uncertainty: IVE method, 2-sigma value (2 x Uncertainty Value reported in *.ft File). @ -Cut taken where sub line enters gauge pool about 1m from shore.  -Cut value confirmed by line frozen on rod. Mid-section

HG: 9.741 SRC: 0.001 No Reset (NR)

column12: Measurement condition : Ice; Cloudy , Moderate Snow , Light Wind Blowing Cross Stream
column13:
-B conditions possible Still looks clear at control but ice just above water level and slush around shore.
-Ice directly above transect and complete cover of pool that sensor is in.
column14: -Side channel running. Measured. -The profile of the measurement has the side channel on the wrong side. Values should be unaffected but graphs of collection data will be backwards. Both channels measured from RHB to LHB. -Alternate measurement section below dropoff is covered in slush and ice. -Cut taken through hole chiselled in ice - approx 2-3cm thick. No surge or fluctuations observed. Mid-section
